# macro_empty_body_test.deor
# Exercises expand_deor_macros' check that a `macro` declaration must have an
# indented body. Without this check, an empty 'macro name' with no block left
# the body-collection loop with no INDENT to balance against, so it ran away
# consuming the rest of the file as its "body" — main() would silently vanish
# into a never-called macro instead of erroring.

macro empty_macro

fn void main()
	print("hi")

# expect-error:
# macro 'empty_macro' - must have an indented body
